node.title: Australia stun Pakistan, will meet Blackcaps in T20 World Cup final
node.description: A trans-Tasman showdown will decide the winner of this year's T20 World Cup.
node.content: ["Australia has reached the Twenty20 World Cup final with a five-wicket victory over Pakistan in the second semi-final on Friday.", "Set 177 for victory, David Warner made 49 before Australia rode unbeaten cameos from Marcus Stoinis (40 not out) and Matthew Wade (41 not out) to clinch the win with one over to spare.", "Earlier, Mohammad Rizwan and Fakhar Zaman smashed breezy half-centuries to help Pakistan post 176/4 at the Dubai International Stadium.", "Put in to bat, Pakistan got off to a strong start with Rizwan (67) and skipper Babar Azam (39) forging a 71-run partnership for the opening wicket.", "Fakhar provided the late charge for the 2009 champions with an unbeaten 55 off 32 balls.", "New Zealand beat England in the first semi-final in Abu Dhabi on Thursday.", "\u00a0"]
